y surface to without cracking due to structural movement as well as thermal expansion and contraction;</li>\n	<li>Preserves against general degradation;</li>\n	<li>Reduces maintenance costs; and</li>\n	<li>Decorates and upgrades any building structure.</li>\n</ol>\n<b>S-26 Concrete and Masonry</b>\n\nThis product is a solvent-based, fully waterproof floor coating well suited to high-traffic areas such as balconies, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">walls </span>(link to walls), garage floors, and parkades. Once applied, it creates a seamless floor casing resistant to UV damage, freeze/thaw conditions and a variety of chemicals and lubricants.','Walls','','inherit','open','open','','78-autosave','','','2013-01-27 19:48:21','2013-01-28 02:48:21','',78,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/2013/01/27/78-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(81,1,'2013-01-27 20:20:37','2013-01-28 03:20:37','Buccaneer offers a cold process roofing system suitable for a wide cross-section of roofing substrates from flat to fully pitched roofs.\r\n\r\n<b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Sloped Roofing</span></b>\r\n\r\n<b>S-26 Storm Seal LD</b>\r\n\r\nThis liquid plastic is a distinctive cold process roofing product that is able to stretch and flex with a wide cross-section of sloped roof substrates through extreme temperature changes. This product’s lightfast pigments will retain colour and protect its substrate against the harshest of elements including: ultraviolet light, snow, rain, and chemical pollution. It can be applied to any existing tile, metal, wood, metal, fiberglass, or asbestos roof.\r\n\r\n<b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Flat Roofing</span></b>\r\n\r\n<b>S-26 Storm Seal HD</b>\r\n\r\nThis product is an integral component of Buccaneer’s cold process roofing system. It works by forming a thick plastic skin that will remain flexible and durable while waterproofing virtually any roofing substrate including: concrete, concrete tiles, steel, wood, and asbestos.\r\n\r\nWhile developing S-26 Storm Seal HD, Buccaneer focused on the foundation of the product - a Waterproof material capable of adhering to a wide cross section of substrate, with sufficient strength to bridge hairline cracks and flexibility to accommodate expansion and contraction.\r\n\r\nOur proprietary resin and high quality pigments work to preserve this unique blend of characteristics over extended periods of exposure to the harshest ultraviolet light, environmental conditions.\r\n\r\n<b>S-26 Storm Seal VHD</b>\r\n\r\nA derivative of S-26 Storm Seal HD, this product incorporates plastic fibers into the mastic thereby increasing its tensile strength. Well suited for seams, joints, and transition areas were high stress torsional forces may concentrate.\r\n\r\n<b>Base Coats</b>\r\n\r\nWhere required, Buccaneer draws on a selection of base coats to suite a full spectrum of roofing substrates.\r\n\r\n<b>Polyester Fabrics</b>\r\n\r\nUtilized in particularly demanding applications where extra waterproofing measures are warranted. Such surfaces include steel roof seams, joints and roof/wall transitions. Our cold seal roofing process can incorporate the use of polyester fabrics between consecutive coats of Storm Seal.\r\n\r\n<i>This product is 100% environmentally friendly, is water soluble, and contains ultra-low levels of V.O.C.’s.</i>','Roofing','','publish','closed','closed','','roofing','','','2013-01-27 21:37:19','2013-01-28 04:37:19','',0,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/?post_type=application&#038;p=81',0,'application','',0),(82,1,'2013-01-27 20:21:17','2013-01-28 03:21:17','Wood is a unique surface because it is a natural material that expands, contracts, absorbs water, and warps long after it has been hewn from a tree. Wood products are vulnerable to sunlight, insect infestation, moisture and general age degradation. Therefore, it is important for any wood preservation product to not only protect against this damage but also be able to move and flex continuously with the wood. Buccaneer’s range of wood preservation products are a unique blend of water-soluble plastic polymers that are durable and have a simple application process. They can be used on new or existing wooden structures.\r\n\r\n<b>S-26 Plastic Wood Preservative</b>\r\n\r\nThis water borne, ultra-low VOC product is unlike any other available wood coating. It is designed for all vertical external woodwork including: garage doors, fencing, window frames, and timber homes. S-26 Plastic Wood Preservative works by forming a water resistant, mould and mildew proof barrier that is resistant to ultraviolet degradation. Once this product is applied, it maintains a flexible surface capable of expanding and contracting with the wood in order to prevent cracking during extreme temperature changes.\r\n\r\n<b>S-26 Wooden Deck Coating </b>\r\n\r\nThis product is a derivative of the S-26 Plastic Wood Preservative. S-26 Wooden Deck Coating is a non-slip formula that ensures secure footing even in damp conditions. It was specially formulated to withstand the added rigors of foot traffic and ultra-high ultraviolet exposure.\r\n\r\n<b>S-26 Clear Seal-Wood</b>\r\n\r\nS-26 Clear Seal -Wood is a solvent borne, fully waterproof, clear topcoat utilized to complement S-26 Plastic Wood Preservative in high impact applications such as: outdoor furniture, railings, stair treds and decks. This product is an easy to use, single pack, quick drying formula.','Wood','','publish','closed','closed','','wood','','','2013-01-27 20:52:47','2013-01-28 03:52:47','',0,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/?post_type=application&#038;p=82',0,'application','',0),(83,1,'2013-01-27 20:22:20','2013-01-28 03:22:20','Wood is a unique surface because it is a natural material that expands, contracts, absorbs water, and warps long after it has been hewn from a tree. Wood products are vulnerable to sunlight, insect infestation, moisture and general age degradation. Therefore, it is important for any wood preservation product to not only protect against this damage but also be able to move and flex continuously with the wood. Buccaneer’s range of wood preservation products are a unique blend of water-soluble plastic polymers that are durable and have a simple application process. They can be used on new or existing wooden structures.\n\n<b>S-26 Plastic Wood Preservative</b>\n\nThis water borne, ultra-low VOC product is unlike any other available wood coating. It is designed for all vertical external woodwork including: garage doors, fencing, window frames, and timber homes. S-26 Plastic Wood Preservative works by forming a water resistant, mould and mildew proof barrier that is resistant to ultraviolet degradation. Once this product is applied, it maintains a flexible surface capable of expanding and contracting with the wood in order to prevent cracking during extreme temperature changes.\n\n<b>S-26 Wooden Deck Coating </b>\n\nThis product is a derivative of the S-26 Plastic Wood Preservative. S-26 Wooden Deck Coating is a non-slip formula that ensures secure footing even in damp conditions. It was specially formulated to withstand the added rigors of foot traffic and ultra-high ultraviolet exposure.\n\n<b>S-26 Clear Seal-Wood</b>\n\nS-26 Clear Seal -Wood is a solvent borne, fully waterproof, clear topcoat utilized to complement S-26 Plastic Wood Preservative in high impact applications such as: outdoor furniture, railings, stair treds and decks. This product is an easy to use, single pack, quick drying formula.','','','inherit','open','open','','82-autosave','','','2013-01-27 20:22:20','2013-01-28 03:22:20','',82,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/2013/01/27/82-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(84,1,'2013-01-27 20:24:05','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2013-01-27 20:24:05','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/?post_type=application&p=84',0,'application','',0),(85,1,'2013-01-27 20:25:06','2013-01-28 03:25:06','From face brick to driveways, the S-26 flooring series prevents damage caused by moisture and is resistant to alkalis, ultraviolet light and staining. Each product in this series offers protection against the elements.\r\n\r\n<b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Face Brick, Stone and Floor Sealers</span></b><b>                       </b>\r\n\r\n<b>S-26 Clear Seal - Concrete and Masonry</b>\r\n\r\nThis solvent based product is a penetrating sealant that provides a highly durable, non-yellowing protective film for brick, stonework, terrazzo concrete and existing epoxy finishes.  It prevents damage typically caused by moisture and UV degradation and wear and tear by bonding to the surface and creating a hard wearing, waterproof barrier. S-26 Clear Seal is resistant to alkalis, ultraviolet light and staining. This is one of the most versatile, long-lasting clear plastic coatings ever developed.\r\n\r\n<b>S-26 Plastic Floor Coating</b>\r\n\r\nThis solvent based, single pack, pigmented, plastic floor enamel protects concrete floors, balconies and exterior walkways against wear and tear caused by moisture ingress, ultraviolet radiation and extreme weather conditions. It is extremely tough, hardwearing and waterproof.\r\n\r\n<i>This product is offered in a variety of colours and comes in a non-slip version. </i>\r\n\r\n<b>S-26 Epoxy Floor Enamel</b>\r\n\r\nThis twin pack, pigmented, plastic floor enamel is ideal for high traffic areas prone to exposure to solvents, lubricants and other potentially corrosive fluids. It is a heavy-duty seamless floor cladding that is resistant to many harsh solvents and chemicals.  Apply this enamel to floors and walls in shops or processing areas to create a seamless, sealed coating between floor and wall.\r\n\r\n<b>S-26 Water Based Floor Coating</b>\r\n\r\nThis single pack, pigmented, plastic product has a highly durable, non-slip finish ideally suited for use in areas such as stairwells, mechanical rooms, storage areas and other confined spaces where fume buildup may pose a fire or inhalation hazard. Also, Ulta-low volatile organic compound (VOC) makes for odorless application.','Floors & Driveways','','publish','closed','closed','','floors-driveways','','','2013-01-27 20:52:57','2013-01-28 03:52:57','',0,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/?post_type=application&#038;p=85',0,'application','',0),(86,1,'2013-01-27 20:25:27','2013-01-28 03:25:27','<b>S-26 Concrete and Masonry</b>\r\n\r\nThis product is a solvent-based, fully waterproof floor coating well suited to high-traffic areas such as balconies, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">walls </span>(link to walls), garage floors, and parkades. Once applied, it creates a seamless floor casing resistant to UV damage, freeze/thaw conditions and a variety of chemicals and lubricants.','Decks & Balconies','','publish','closed','closed','','decks-balconies','','','2013-01-27 20:53:16','2013-01-28 03:53:16','',0,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/?post_type=application&#038;p=86',0,'application','',0),(87,1,'2013-01-27 20:26:28','2013-01-28 03:26:28','<b>S-26 Concrete and Masonry</b>\n\nThis product is a solvent-based, fully waterproof floor coating well suited to high-traffic areas such as balconies, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">walls </span>(link to walls), garage floors, and parkades. Once applied, it creates a seamless floor casing resistant to UV damage, freeze/thaw conditions and a variety of chemicals and lubricants.','Decks & Balconies','','inherit','open','open','','86-autosave','','','2013-01-27 20:26:28','2013-01-28 03:26:28','',86,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/2013/01/27/86-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(88,1,'2013-01-27 20:29:48','2013-01-28 03:29:48','<b>S-26 Plastic Crack Filler</b>\r\n\r\nThis product can be used in any type of crack or void to repair damage in minutes.  This water soluble formulation is environmentally friendly. Unlike powdered crack fillers, the S-26 Plastic Crack Filler is flexible, waterproof and will move with a structure’s substrata to prevent future cracking. Where extra hardness is desired, incorporate Portland cement into the crack filler prior to application.  Crack filler can be used with cement, concrete, plasterwork and woodwork, making it one of the most versatile fillers in the world.','Cracks','','publish','closed','closed','','cracks','','','2013-01-27 20:52:11','2013-01-28 03:52:11','',0,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/?post_type=application&#038;p=88',0,'application','',0),(89,1,'2013-01-05 21:47:49','2013-01-06 04:47:49','Based in Calgary, Alberta, Buccaneer Canada is a manufacturer and distributor of <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">liquid plastic coating</span> <i>(link to internal page on liquid applied protection)</i> systems designed to preserve and protect a wide spectrum of building materials and surfaces. Learn more about our <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">applications</span>.\r\n\r\nBuccaneer coating solutions have a 35-year history of development and application in the United Kingdom and South Africa. Over the years applications have spread throughout South Africa, the Benelux Countries, Iceland and Canada.\r\n\r\nAt Buccaneer, our mission is to produce the highest quality coatings utilizing our proprietary formulations with uncompromising raw material inputs. Combing ease of use and superior durability provides a cost effective and long term coating solution for our customers while respecting the environment by using only eco-friendly acceptable raw materials that are not hazardous to people, animals or the environment.','About','','inherit','open','open','','38-revision-2','','','2013-01-05 21:47:49','2013-01-06 04:47:49','',38,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/2013/01/05/38-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(90,1,'2013-01-27 20:33:25','2013-01-28 03:33:25','<b>Architectural and Industrial Coating Systems</b>\r\n\r\nOne of the first questions we typically get at Buccaneer is “why plastic, why not paint?”. Our plastic architectural and industrial coating systems have proved themselves as far more durable than conventional paints and varnishes.\r\n\r\nPlastics do not degrade over time or become a hazard. Instead, they protect and preserve the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">surfaces</span> <i>(link to applications)</i> to which they are applied.\r\n\r\nExtensive research and development has led to the advancement of proprietary resins and entirely unique formulations. Buccaneer Architectural and Industrial Coating Systems can be applied to all types of <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">surfaces</span> <i>(link to applications)</i> including steel, wood, concrete and plaster. The unique chemical formula of this product line allows for maximum durability that will outperform virtually all conventional paint products and give any building or structure a far superior life span dramatically reducing expensive maintenance costs.\r\n\r\nBuccaneer offers both water-borne and solvent-borne protective coating solutions based on the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">application</span> required.','Coating Systems','','publish','open','open','','coating-systems','','','2013-01-27 20:33:25','2013-01-28 03:33:25','',0,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/?page_id=90',0,'page','',0),(91,1,'2013-01-27 20:33:24','2013-01-28 03:33:24','<b>Architectural and Industrial Coating Systems</b>\n\nOne of the first questions we typically get at Buccaneer is “why plastic, why not paint?”. Our plastic architectural and industrial coating systems have proved themselves as far more durable than conventional paints and varnishes.\n\nPlastics do not degrade over time or become a hazard. Instead, they protect and preserve the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">surfaces</span> <i>(link to applications)</i> to which they are applied.\n\nExtensive research and development has led to the advancement of proprietary resins and entirely unique formulations. Buccaneer Architectural and Industrial Coating Systems can be applied to all types of <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">surfaces</span> <i>(link to applications)</i> including steel, wood, concrete and plaster. The unique chemical formula of this product line allows for maximum durability that will outperform virtually all conventional paint products and give any building or structure a far superior life span dramatically reducing expensive maintenance costs.\n\nBuccaneer offers both water-borne and solvent-borne protective coating solutions based on the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">application</span> required.','Coating Systems','','inherit','open','open','','90-revision','','','2013-01-27 20:33:24','2013-01-28 03:33:24','',90,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/2013/01/27/90-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(92,1,'2013-01-27 20:33:49','2013-01-28 03:33:49',' ','','','publish','open','open','','92','','','2013-01-27 20:36:06','2013-01-28 03:36:06','',0,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/?p=92',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(93,1,'2013-01-27 20:34:22','2013-01-28 03:34:22','','Overview','','publish','open','open','','overview','','','2013-01-27 20:36:06','2013-01-28 03:36:06','',0,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/?p=93',6,'nav_menu_item','',0),(94,1,'2013-01-27 20:35:59','2013-01-28 03:35:59','','Applications','','publish','open','open','','applications','','','2013-01-27 20:36:06','2013-01-28 03:36:06','',0,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/?p=94',5,'nav_menu_item','',0),(95,1,'2013-01-27 20:35:59','2013-01-28 03:35:59',' ','','','publish','open','open','','95','','','2013-01-27 20:36:06','2013-01-28 03:36:06','',0,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/?p=95',12,'nav_menu_item','',0),(96,1,'2013-01-27 20:35:59','2013-01-28 03:35:59',' ','','','publish','open','open','','96','','','2013-01-27 20:36:06','2013-01-28 03:36:06','',0,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/?p=96',11,'nav_menu_item','',0),(97,1,'2013-01-27 20:35:59','2013-01-28 03:35:59',' ','','','publish','open','open','','97','','','2013-01-27 20:36:06','2013-01-28 03:36:06','',0,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/?p=97',10,'nav_menu_item','',0),(98,1,'2013-01-27 20:35:59','2013-01-28 03:35:59',' ','','','publish','open','open','','98','','','2013-01-27 20:36:06','2013-01-28 03:36:06','',0,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/?p=98',9,'nav_menu_item','',0),(99,1,'2013-01-27 20:35:59','2013-01-28 03:35:59',' ','','','publish','open','open','','99','','','2013-01-27 20:36:06','2013-01-28 03:36:06','',0,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/?p=99',8,'nav_menu_item','',0),(100,1,'2013-01-27 20:35:59','2013-01-28 03:35:59',' ','','','publish','open','open','','100','','','2013-01-27 20:36:06','2013-01-28 03:36:06','',0,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/?p=100',7,'nav_menu_item','',0),(101,1,'2013-01-27 21:23:59','2013-01-28 04:23:59','','buccaneer_test','','inherit','open','open','','buccaneer_test','','','2013-01-27 21:23:59','2013-01-28 04:23:59','',81,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/buccaneer_test.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(102,1,'2013-01-27 21:38:22','2013-01-28 04:38:22','Buccaneer offers a cold process roofing system suitable for a wide cross-section of roofing substrates from flat to fully pitched roofs.\n\n<b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Sloped Roofing</span></b>\n\n<b>S-26 Storm Seal LD</b>\n\nThis liquid plastic is a distinctive cold process roofing product that is able to stretch and flex with a wide cross-section of sloped roof substrates through extreme temperature changes. This product’s lightfast pigments will retain colour and protect its substrate against the harshest of elements including: ultraviolet light, snow, rain, and chemical pollution. It can be applied to any existing tile, metal, wood, metal, fiberglass, or asbestos roof.\n\n<b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Flat Roofing</span></b>\n\n<b>S-26 Storm Seal HD</b>\n\nThis product is an integral component of Buccaneer’s cold process roofing system. It works by forming a thick plastic skin that will remain flexible and durable while waterproofing virtually any roofing substrate including: concrete, concrete tiles, steel, wood, and asbestos.\n\nWhile developing S-26 Storm Seal HD, Buccaneer focused on the foundation of the product - a Waterproof material capable of adhering to a wide cross section of substrate, with sufficient strength to bridge hairline cracks and flexibility to accommodate expansion and contraction.\n\nOur proprietary resin and high quality pigments work to preserve this unique blend of characteristics over extended periods of exposure to the harshest ultraviolet light, environmental conditions.\n\n<b>S-26 Storm Seal VHD</b>\n\nA derivative of S-26 Storm Seal HD, this product incorporates plastic fibers into the mastic thereby increasing its tensile strength. Well suited for seams, joints, and transition areas were high stress torsional forces may concentrate.\n\n<b>Base Coats</b>\n\nWhere required, Buccaneer draws on a selection of base coats to suite a full spectrum of roofing substrates.\n\n<b>Polyester Fabrics</b>\n\nUtilized in particularly demanding applications where extra waterproofing measures are warranted. Such surfaces include steel roof seams, joints and roof/wall transitions. Our cold seal roofing process can incorporate the use of polyester fabrics between consecutive coats of Storm Seal.\n\n<i>This product is 100% environmentally friendly, is water soluble, and contains ultra-low levels of V.O.C.’s.</i>','Roofing','','inherit','open','open','','81-autosave','','','2013-01-27 21:38:22','2013-01-28 04:38:22','',81,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/2013/01/27/81-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(103,1,'2013-01-27 21:29:43','2013-01-28 04:29:43','','buccaneer_test','','inherit','open','open','','buccaneer_test-2','','','2013-01-27 21:29:43','2013-01-28 04:29:43','',81,'http://buccaneercoatings.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/buccaneer_test1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(104,1,'2013-01-27 21:37:14','2013-01-28 04:37:14','','buccaneer_test','','inh